author: Mohd Indra
text:
- Small and compact gym. It has 2 level, split in free weight section and machine weight, walking distance from MRT, polyclinic (if you need) and food places. I will expect that peak hours will be extremely squeeze.

- Cardio Machine are facing the road and the walk way so kind of a sad view and people will definitely look at you

- Went on a weekend mid-day, wasnt crowed, can say 6 machine on each floors were occupied with people.

- Equipment wise all are from Hammer or Life Fitness and still new as of today.

- Bag storage wise not a lot, majority of them are found at level 2.

- Only 4 bathroom, has both shower and toilet located at level 2.

Level 1 machine weight
- 1 stairmill
- 4 treadmills
- 2 exercise bike
- 2 elliptical
- 1 functional trainer machine
- 1 lat/row combo machine
- 1 crunch machine
- 1 preacher curl machine
- 1 fixed lat pull-down machine
- 1 leg extension
- 1 seated leg press
- 1 prone leg curl
- 1 pec fly machine
- 1 standing calf raise
- 1 pull-up/dip tower
- 1 fixed bench if you want to do bench press at the power rack
Etc....

Level 2
- 2 power rack
- 1 smith rack
- 1 deadlift platform
- 1 hip trust
- 2 adjustable bench
- 1 preacher curl
- 1 row machine
- 1 leg press
Etc....

Small functional area

author: john ng
text: Very disappointing experience with this gym. Unlike other gyms that allow walk-in trials, this one insists on a one-day advance booking ‚Äî yet even after following that rule and emailing as instructed, I was rejected twice. Each time, I was told they were understaffed. If you can‚Äôt accommodate trial bookings even with advance notice, then don‚Äôt advertise them. Poor organization and lack of reliability left a bad first impression.

author: Nathanael Khoo
text:
Hands down the best gym in the north of Singapore.

The ambiance and attention to detail to the decor is top notch. The machines are also strategically placed. First floor for machines and second floor for free weights. Love how the management invested into Hammer Strength equipment as well. Their machines are top-notch man.

You can tell the management did some really great planning.

I was working out and saw a gigachad pressing 45kg dumbbells. You know the gym is great if a gigachad like him chooses to workout here.

For me, it's an awesome place to sweat it out and become aesthetic af. Just being here motivates me.

author: Andy
text: The best anytime fitness gym. I‚Äôm not writing this review because I was told to but because I want to. Their staff are friendly and approachable with really professional advice. Love the cleanliness of this new gym. Lots of machine with unique exercises. Although it can be small but very cozy and usually not full. They don‚Äôt hard sell and won‚Äôt charge you for anything extra unlike some other gym at woodlands where they will find any opportunity to charge you I think soon they might charge for water too if they can. Marsiling mrt gym is the best by far.

author: Spartan Dan
text:
One of the best AF I've been too. Though space rather small. It's still enough to move around freely.
2 squat racks, one deadlift platform. Plenty of weights.
And best of all 5 toilets. Wah this one most AF lost at this. 2 water coolers as well.
Keep it up. Might be the AF I'll go for in the north.

author: Barry Pereira
text: Good machines and very friendly staff. Clean too

author: Fabian Ong
text: Small and cozy gym, well equipped with more machines coming soon. Really love the overall vibes of the gym. Just a short distance from Marsiling mrt, facing Marsiling polyclinic.

author: Sashir Karasu -
text: The best, been going there for awhile now. Nice place, clean and friendly. Feels like your own personal gym and feels like home.
